</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2247_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Document observations as soon as they are made to ensure accuracy and relevance.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2249_">Use standardised terminology
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2251_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Employ clear, standardised language to avoid misunderstandings.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2253_">Ensure readability
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2255_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Handwritten notes must be legible; electronic entries must be clear and concise.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2257_">Be comprehensive yet relevant
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2259_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Include all necessary information without overloading the record with irrelevant details.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2261_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2262_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2263_">Common pitfalls and avoidance strategies
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_b4c6dd93-03ab-425f-9887-cc242a50e41d.png?v=1709889469" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_b4c6dd93-03ab-425f-9887-cc242a50e41d.png?v=1709889469 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_b4c6dd93-03ab-425f-9887-cc242a50e41d_1000x.png?v=1709889469 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_b4c6dd93-03ab-425f-9887-cc242a50e41d_500x.png?v=1709889469 320w" width="1456" height="971" alt="Improving Healthcare Practices: Quality Assurance in Clinical Documentation - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Improving Healthcare Practices: Quality Assurance in Clinical Documentation - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-2265_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2266_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by AtlasComposer via Envato Elements</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2268_">Incomplete records
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2270_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Ensure all fields are filled. Use checklists as reminders.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2272_">Subjectivity
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2274_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Stick to objective data. If subjective descriptions are necessary, clearly label them as such.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2276_">Illegibility in handwritten notes
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2278_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Opt for electronic documentation or care for handwriting clarity.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-2280_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-2281_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-2282_">The role of EHRs in enhancing documentation
