</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-2289_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2290_"><b>Improved accuracy</b> - Templates and dropdown menus reduce the risk of incomplete or inaccurate entries.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2292_"><b>Enhanced accessibility</b> - Patient information is readily available to authorised personnel across different settings.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-2294_"><b>Data security </b>- Advanced encryption methods protect sensitive patient information from unauthorised access.
</li></ul><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-2296_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Implementation of EHRs has been shown to improve the accuracy of patient documentation by up to 50%.
